race.comment: SIMPLY STYLISH (2) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by 3 lengths at Healesville in a handy 19.37 beating Canny Lass. The hardest to beat again. PAW JUDAS (7) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by half a length at Warrnambool in a handy 22.27 beating Saint Tay. Has hit winning form and can go on with it. MARKET JET (1) produced a modest effort most recently when sixth at this track over 450m behind Go Go Evie (25.78) in a Grade 5. Form from his last run is proving strong. One of the better chances. PEGASUS BALE (3) was strongly fancied on the back of a win two starts back but finished third last time (23.32) at Warragul.
